On 10/26/04 9:09 PM, "Zach Freshman" <zachary(-at-)freshmans.com> wrote:

> Front wheel bearings need to be changed. How do I get the outer bearing
> out of there. It tried St Muirs method of using a cold chisel and brute
> force, but I couldn't get a good "bite" on it. Do I just bite the bullet
> and take it to my local VW Shop

Invest in tools. For removal use a brass drift. They Mayhew set from Sears
is a good price. Search craftsman.com for item# 61360.

For installation get the Lisle bearing driver set (also at Sears):

Item# 12600

http://www.lislecorp.com/tool_browse_list.cfm?browse=7

